[{"id":"FT4108","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p>Assume the elevator is moving at constant speed, and consider the bottom box in the stack that has two boxes of mass 2<em>M</em>. Let <em>F</em><sub>floor</sub> be the force exerted by the floor on the box, <em>F<sub>g</sub></em> be the force exerted by gravity on the box, and <em>F</em><sub>box</sub> be the force exerted by the top box on the bottom box. Which of the following best represents the forces exerted on the bottom box?</p>","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p>Refer to the following material to answer the questions.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"The figure shows four columns, each with two boxes, one on top of the other, all inside a single large rectangle.  Each box has a labeled mass.    From left to right, in the first column are 2 boxes of equal size and each labeled M. In the second column, the box on top appears to be larger than the box on bottom.  The top box is labeled 2M and the bottom box is labeled M.  In the third column are 2 boxes of equal size and each labeled 2M. In the fourth column, the box on top appears to be larger than the box on bottom. The top box is labeled 4M and the bottom box is labeled 2M. \" height=\"122\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/ddca865d01cb8e85cc7ff7bcb014354c/original.png\" width=\"240\" /></p>\n\n<p>The stacks of boxes shown in the figure above are inside an elevator that is moving upward. The masses of the boxes are given in terms of the mass <em>M </em>of the lightest box.</p>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<img alt=\"Each option consists of a square box with directional arrows connected to either the top of the box or to the bottom of the box.  Option A. The figure shows a box connected to a vertical arrow pointing up labeled F sub floor, and a vertical arrow pointing down labeled F sub g. The arrows appear to be about equal in length. \" height=\"232\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/668661278ec313a08592e541452d47fb/original.png\" width=\"140\">","<img alt=\"Option B. The figure shows a box connected to a vertical arrow pointing up, labeled F sub floor, and a vertical arrow pointing down labeled F sub box. The arrows appear to be about equal in length. \" height=\"232\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/45704613ee97836979df9c6f9fbd9d7b/original.png\" width=\"140\">","<img alt=\"Option C. The figure shows a box connected to a vertical arrow pointing up labeled F sub floor, and two vertical arrows pointing down which appear to be half the length of the arrow above. The downward arrow below the box and on the left is labeled F sub g, and the downward arrow below the box and on the right is labeled F sub box. \" height=\"190\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/9901f7e24cbed410180ff5f7e737a49c/original.png\" width=\"140\">","<img alt=\"Option D. The figure shows a box connected to two vertical arrows pointing up and a vertical arrow pointing down labeled F sub g. The arrows on top of the box appear to be about half the length of the arrow on the bottom of the box. The upward arrow on top of the box and to the left is labeled F sub box, and the upward arrow on top of the box and to the right is labeled F sub floor. \" height=\"190\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/6db81763a2d52fb9cf0da120173417e8/original.png\" width=\"140\">"],"answer":1}]